\title{Foundations of Data Science}


\section*{Python Objects}



In Python, a data type is like a label for a piece of information that tells the computer how to interpret and work with that information. It helps Python understand what kind of value you're dealing with, such as numbers, text, or a collection of items. This makes it easier to perform operations and manipulate data in a way that makes sense for the specific type of information you have.\\\
\\\

