\section*{Basic Arithmetic Operations}\\\






\subsection*{Addition} \[2+8 = 10\]

\subsection*{Subtraction}
\[4-1 = 3\]

\subsection*{Multiplication}
\[2 * 2 = 4\]

\subsection*{Division}
\[\frac{7}{3} =2.3333333333333335\]

\subsection*{Floor Division}
\[\frac{7}{3}=2\]\\\

\\\ In Python, floor division is a mathematical operation that returns the largest integer less than or equal to the result of the division of two numbers. It is performed using the double forward slash operator \(\text{//}\).

\newpage

\textbf Interview Questions:\\

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{What is a data type in Python?}
    
    \item \textbf{Differentiate between integers and floating-point numbers in Python.}
    
    \item \textbf{Provide an example of an integer in Python.}
    
    \item \textbf{Give an example of a floating-point number in Python.}
    
    \item \textbf{Explain the concept of casting in Python and how it can be used to convert between data types.}
    
    \item \textbf{What is the result of the expression \texttt{3 / 2} in Python, and how can you modify it to get an integer result?}
    
    \item \textbf{How would you check the data type of a variable in Python?}
    
    \item \textbf{What does the \texttt{type()} function do in Python?}
    
    \item \textbf{How can you create a variable that stores a floating-point number with the value 5.0?}
    
    \item \textbf{What is the purpose of using scientific notation for floating-point numbers in Python?}
\end{enumerate}

